headline.main: STUDY LINKS OBESITY TO LEVEL OF INCOME

docs.abstract: Study of 1,660 New Yorkers finds obesity 7 times more frequent among women of lowest socio-econ level; finds men have similar relationship but to lesser degree; finds obese people tend to be less mature, more rigid and suspicious than those of normal weight
docs.lead_paragraph: CHICAGO, Sept. 13 (AP)-- Women with low incomes tend to be more plump than those who are well-to-do, a group of medical researchers reported today.
